[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Asynchronously copies the entire directory structure from `src` to `dest`, including subdirectories and files.When copying a directory to another directory, globs are not supported and behavior is similar to `cp dir1/ dir2/`.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Changes the permissions on a symbolic link.This method is only implemented on macOS.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Changes the ownership on a symbolic link.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Changes the access and modification times of a file in the same way as `fsPromises.utimes()`, with the difference that if the path refers to a symbolic link, then the link is not dereferenced: instead, the timestamps of the symbolic link itself are changed.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Creates a new link from the `existingPath` to the `newPath`.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] See the POSIX `link(2)` documentation for more detail.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Equivalent to `fsPromises.stat()` unless `path` refers to a symbolic link, in which case the link itself is stat-ed, not the file that it refers to.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Refer to the POSIX `lstat(2)` document for more detail.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Asynchronously creates a directory.The optional `options` argument can be an integer specifying `mode` (permission and sticky bits), or an object with a `mode` property and a `recursive` property indicating whether parent directories should be created.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] A unique directory name is generated by appending six random characters to the end of the provided `prefix`.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Due to platform inconsistencies, avoid trailing `X` characters in `prefix`.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] For instance, given a directory `/tmp`, if the intention is to create a temporary directory *within* `/tmp`, the `prefix` must end with a trailing platform-specific path separator (`require('node:path').sep`).
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] The resulting Promise holds an async-disposable object whose `path` property holds the created directory path.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] When the object is disposed, the directory and its contents will be removed asynchronously if it still exists.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] If the directory cannot be deleted, disposal will throw an error.
